		<p>The following folders are in Box 502:<lb/>
		Fuel Advisory committee - Minutes of Meetings<lb/>
		Fuel - Correspondence with: Mayors, First Selectmen Re: Fuel Committees' Conservation<lb/>
		Fuel - Correspondence with Newspapers Re: Governor's speech on Fuel, 1/5/1948. Also copy of speech.<lb/>
		Fuel - Correspondence with Oil Companies Re: Fuel Supplies &amp; Reservation of Heating Fuels<lb/>
		Fuel - Correspondence with President, Secretary of Commerce, Navy Department, Department of Interior, Maritime Commission, and Congressional delegates<lb/></p>

	<p>The following folders are in Box 503:<lb/>
		Fuel - General File<lb/>					
		Fuel - Reports from State Department Re: Conservation Of Fuel<lb/>
		Fuel - Texas Oil Strike Correspondence with President, Congressional Delegates, American Oil Company, And Governor Robert Bradford [MA]<lb/></p>

	<p><emph render="bold">RG 050, War Council, 1940-1945, (see especially the Fuel Section file, which includes papers of the Fuel Adminstrator).</emph>
</p>
